<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=118&amp;p=721#p721"><![CDATA[
You can make SBC always work by implementing SBC in terms of ADC: load the operand from memory as normal, invert it (^ 0xff), and then do your ADC code. Reducing complexity of your emulator's 6502 core is a good thing.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat Dec 25, 2004 2:38 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
