<author><name><![CDATA[Disch]]></name></author>
<updated>2004-12-25T10:45:04-07:00</updated>
<published>2004-12-25T10:45:04-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=118&amp;p=720#p720</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=118&amp;p=720#p720"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Mario Sprites Problem]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=118&amp;p=720#p720"><![CDATA[
Sounds almost like a V flag problem (bad wrapping at 128 could be because the V flag is being set wrong on ADC/SBC)<br /><br />Double check your ADC/SBC.  For ADC... the V flag should be set when:<br /><br />Positive + Positive = Negative<br />or<br />Negative + Negative = Positive<br /><br />In all other instances of ADC, the V flag should be cleared.<br /><br /><br />Likewise for SBC... V flag is set when:<br /><br />Positive - Negative = Negative<br />or<br />Negative - Positive = Positive<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=33">Disch</a> — Sat Dec 25, 2004 10:45 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
